Ques: It is a matter of common knowledge that 0 degree celcius is same as 32degree farenheit. It is also known fact that 100 degree celcius equals 212 degree farenheit. 
But there is a temperature taht gives the same reading ob both centigrade and farenhiet scale. Can you find this temperature?

Solu: If X is the temperature 9X/5=X-32
i.e 4X/5 =-32
which gives X=-40 
which means -40degree celcius = -40degree farenheit
